## `<file-level: options structs>`
<!-- checksum: rust-mkfs-1 -->

### Purpose
Python's keyword arguments become Rust `Options` structs with `Default` impls. Two: `MkfsOptions` for first-time creation, `OpenOptions` for subsequent open.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
use std::time::Duration;
use crate::schema::{SyncMode, DEFAULT_CHUNK_SIZE};

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct MkfsOptions {
    pub chunk_size: i64,
    pub overwrite: bool,
    pub owner_uid: Option<u32>,
    pub owner_gid: Option<u32>,
}

impl Default for MkfsOptions {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            chunk_size: DEFAULT_CHUNK_SIZE,
            overwrite: false,
            owner_uid: None,
            owner_gid: None,
        }
    }
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default)]
pub struct OpenOptions {
    pub readonly: bool,
    pub uid: Option<u32>,
    pub gid: Option<u32>,
    pub sync_mode: SyncMode,                    // plan.v7: Default = Normal
    pub checkpoint_interval: Option<Duration>,  // plan.v6
}
```

